              "free_text": [
                "",
                " Two samples of Au are:",
                " First: purity - 99.99% , weight - 122.84g , diam. -",
                "5.115cm, thickness - 0.315cm, density - 19.282g/cm3,",
                "molecular weight - 196.97g, areal density - 1.7633.",
                " Second: purity - 99.99% , weight - 117.34g , diam. -",
                "5.090cm, thickness - 0.310cm, density - 19.282g/cm3,",
                "molecular weight - 196.97g, areal density - 1.8280.",
                "Cross sections of Au are references without",
                "uncertainties for calculating the cross sections of",
                "63Cu and 186W. These reference data were obtained by",
                "fitting ENDF-6 data about Au(n,gamma) reaction with",
                "polinomial. (Authors comment)"
              ]
            }
